Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Mix onion, bell pepper, bread crumbs, hot pepper sauce, egg, salt, and pepper together in a large bowl. Add ground beef; mix. Press beef mixture into a loaf pan. Sprinkle brown gravy mix over meat. Bake in preheated oven until cooked through and browned, 1 hour. Remove from oven and let rest for 10 minutes before serving.